Algorithm

Prompt user for- “name”
prompt user for -"Taxcode"
prompt user for -"Sales amount"
Store all inputs from user
Check for tax codes: -
1.	If user inputs taxcode “0”-Tax exempt
2.	If user inputs taxcode“1” –Calculates tax amt
3.	If user inputs tax code "3 “-Calculates tax amt
4. if user inputs taxcode "other"- displays the error message and re-prompt the user
At the end detail sales report displays with taxcode,customername,sales amt,tax amt and total amt

Pseudocode
step 1: Initialize an empty string,int and double
step 2: Construct a new “Scanner” object
Step 3: prompt the user
Step 4: Get the user input
Step 5: If user prompts correct
	process tax amount
	If user prompts wrong with wrong value
	displays the error messagea nd prompts the suer again
end if
print the sales report as a heading
print the detail sales report 
	System quits
	else
	Display error message and re-prompts again
	End if
End while
